\section{Width guidelines}{

Landscape Letter paper (11 × 8.5 in) with 1 in margins gives \strong{9 in}
of printable width. A common pharma layout:\tabular{ll}{
   Column type \tab Typical width \cr
   Stub / row label \tab 2.0–3.0 in \cr
   Treatment arm (n, \%) \tab 1.2–1.5 in \cr
   P-value \tab 0.8–1.0 in \cr
   Total column \tab 1.2–1.5 in \cr
}


Use \code{width = "auto"} to let the layout engine calculate these from
content, or set fixed widths for exact control.
}

\section{Alignment conventions}{

Standard pharma house styles (Roche, Novartis, Pfizer TFL guides):
\itemize{
\item \strong{Stub / parameter column}: left-aligned.
\item \strong{Count and percentage columns}: right-aligned or decimal-aligned.
\item \strong{P-value columns}: right-aligned or decimal-aligned.
\item \strong{Category columns} (Yes/No, Male/Female): centered or left-aligned.
}
}

\section{N-count precedence}{

